data.3-configure-pre-tool-hooks#3. Configure:
Hooks are deterministic checks that run before Claude calls a tool. If the hook exits non-zero, the tool call is blocked — the model literally cannot do the thing. Put hooks in .claude/settings.json.
{ "hooks": { "PreToolUse": [ { "matcher": "Edit|Write", "hooks": [ { "type": "command", "command": ".claude/hooks/block-risky-paths.sh" }, { "type": "command", "command": ".claude/hooks/require-test-if-code.sh" } ] }, { "matcher": "Bash", "hooks": [ { "type": "command", "command": ".claude/hooks/no-dangerous-shell.sh" } ] } ], "PostToolUse": [ { "matcher": "Edit|Write", "hooks": [ { "type": "command", "command": ".claude/hooks/scan-secrets.sh" } ] } ] } } Example hook: .claude/hooks/block-risky-paths.sh
#!/usr/bin/env bash set -euo pipefail # Reads the pending tool call from stdin as JSON. INPUT=$(cat) PATH_ARG=$(echo "$INPUT" | jq -r '.tool_input.file_path // empty') case "$PATH_ARG" in */migrations/*|*/terraform/*|*.generated.*) echo "BLOCKED: $PATH_ARG is in a protected path (see CLAUDE.md)" >&2 exit 2 ;; esac exit 0 Hooks are trust boundaries. Anything that would be catastrophic to get wrong (lockfile edits during a non-dep-bump task, writes to migrations/, pushes to main) belongs in a hook — not in a prompt instruction. The model can ignore a prompt; it cannot override a hook.

